r the jewelry  it s anyone s guess as to whether or not its method of disposal was purposeful  Partin thinks not  at least in most cases   But I m not going to go searching for the owner  she commented   Once it s gone  it s gone  Partin came to VMI as a biology major  but discovered during her 4th Class year that her true calling was in engineering  It didn t hurt that her brother  Johnny Partin  14  was also a civil engineering major  In the summer of 2014  Allison Partin traveled to Bolivia with the Keydets Without Borders group led by Lt  Col  Tim Moore II  97  associate professor of civil and environmental engineering  There  as she helped build latrine shower combinations for villagers who had never before had indoor plumbing  Partin felt herself drawn to the environmental side of engineering  As the summer of 2015 approached  Partin went to Capt  John  Ned  Riester  78  head of the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering  and asked about internship possibilities  As head of the Maury Service Authority  the regional entity in charge of the municipal water supply for the city of Lexington and parts of Rockbridge County  Riester has good connections  and it wasn t long before Partin had secured her position in Buena Vista  When June 1 arrived  and Partin showed up for her first day of work  she wasn t sure if she d made the right decision  She recalled her first thought   It smells awful  I can t believe I m working here  Soon  though  Partin found herself adjusting to the smell  which she said is confined to certain parts of the plant  She also found herself enjoying both the work and her co workers  Of the latter  she noted   The people I work with are great  They re hilarious  We joke about it  saying   At least we all smell the same  Arriving at 6 30 a m  each scheduled work day  Partin immediately goes to work testing water samples to ensure that pH levels are within the normal range  both for water coming in and water going out   If it s not in a specific range  we really do have a problem that has to be addressed right now  she noted  Later tasks include serving as the  sludge judge  who inspects solid wastes as they re in the process of dehydrating  so the plant operator will know when it s time to have the wastes hauled away in a dump truck  Partin and Trina Mastran  the city s director of water quality  have also been testing phosphorous and nitrogen levels in the water  as the state Department of Environmental Quality sets limits on how much of these elements can be released into the Chesapeake Bay watershed  Riester noted that for a budding engineer  this kind of experience is invaluable   Most of the internships are pretty good  but every now and then you hear about one where they say   Oh  I just made coffee  he commented   I knew from talking to Trina that she d be a great mentor and help  Partin  get her hands dirty    It s just a great opportunity  Partin agreed  noting that she s now considering a multitude of possibilities for after graduation  among them working at a wastewater treatment plant near her hometown of Chester  or possibly going to graduate school for environmental engineering or petroleum engineering  No matter which way she goes  Partin is grateful that her path has included a stint in the wastewater treatment plant   I just don t think people see the opportunities  wastewater treatment  has  she said   People always judge it and say   I don t want to deal with human waste  but   you re basically making the water safe for an entire city   Mary Price  VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  